body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Dylan Martin from SafeRide Car Dealership. May I know your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Janet. Can you provide me with your date of birth for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's zero five / one zero / one nine eight zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And can you also provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's seven eight nine zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing that information, Janet. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Janet. If you have any more questions, feel free to reach out. Have a wonderful day!
